<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Gelum Fyre:
[B]I like the idea in general.  Perhaps "governing" (or a better term) could be created as a trade skill.  Obviously there will be some level of "dedication" when one has to place XP into such trait to obtain a higher level of town service.

Maybe this trait could be applied 100% in ONE town, 50% in other same-race towns, and 10% in other towns.  Just by having "governing" as a usable skill could label you as a "representative" of that town (and race).  Higher levels could equate to ambassador.  A higher level of one town (Mayor of a new Aluvian town) could equate to an ambassador of other race towns and perhaps an offical of somesort in other same race towns.

Just rollin with the ideas.  Someone, help me focus!   ;)[/B][/QUOTE]

